		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Jewish Chronicle Office</placeName>&#44;</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>24&#44; HOUNDSDITCH</placeName>.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>London</placeName>&#44; <date>8 Septr 1852</date></p>
				<p>Dear Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">On the other side I beg to hand you<lb/> the account for advertisements in the Jewish<lb/> Chronicle for the congregation at <placeName>Mobile</placeName> &#38;<lb/> <placeName>Savannah</placeName> <add>&#63;</add> to orders in the Occident<lb/> I shall be happy to forward you a<lb/> copy of the Prose Essays on the Post<lb/> Biblical History of the Jews as soon<lb/> as you will let me know through<lb/> whom it can be forwarded.</p>
				<p>&#42; &#42; Post Office Orders are requested to be made payable to the order of <persName>Joseph Mitchell</persName>.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am not aware whether<lb/> the advertisements have met such<lb/> a response but I am opinion that<lb/> there has been not from <placeName>England</placeName><lb/> &#38; the reason would be obvious<lb/> Young men especially if they be not<lb/> overburdened with cash <sic>cant</sic> afford<lb/> to spend a large sum of money<lb/> on a venture.  In <placeName>England</placeName> a certain<lb/> amount is always allowed for expenses<lb/> for candidates from another country.</p>
				<p>Awaiting your reply which I request<lb/> may be direct to the Jewish Chronicle<lb/> Office  I am Dr Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author"><add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd A Leeser</addressee></p>
